==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neurenteric
<hw>Neu`ren*ter"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Neuro-</ets> + <ets>enteric</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to both the neuron and the enteron; <as>as, the
<ex>neurenteric</ex> canal, which, in embroys of many vertebrates,
connects the medullary tube and the primitive intestine</as>. See
<xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Ectoderm</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>neurergic</ent>⟦br⟧
